<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="13Mar1932"><font color="red">13 March 1932</font> <i>BLHW</i> (to Harriet Weaver): I have been working hard every day &hellip; I ought to go to Zurich, the cataract in the right eye being now total &hellip; I feel personally unworthy of your munificence, of my wife&apos;s constant devotion, of my father&apos;s lifelong and almost piteous pride but I feel quite worthy of Miss Beach&apos;s and Miss Monnier&apos;s friendship and interest </div>
